Secundus gives an historical review of the causes leading to the development of oratory at Rome, viz. the strife of parties and the general political restlessness which agitated the state. Oratory was favored too by the mode of procedure in the courts. Liberal time used to be afforded for speaking, and the number of counsel was not limited‚ whereas to-day every sort of restriction and impediment confronts the advocate.
